                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17070115-12-defend51 t17070115-12-deflabel59"></join>, that the Rooms where the Fire was, were his Chambers, that no Body lay there, that none had Keys to the Doors but himself, and that he was not in the Chamber all that Day, and that therefore he suspected the Prisoner. The Prisoner in his Defence, produced Evidence to prove, step by step where he had been all that Day, as likewise to prove, that he was in Bed at the Prosecutors House, near half a Mile from the Chambers, at 10 a Clock that night; there being no positive Evidence against the Prisoner, the Jury <rs id="t17070115-12-verdict60" type="verdictDescription">
